I"Þ<h1 id="create-a-blank-jekyll-site">Create a Blank Jekyll Site</h1>

<p>To create a new blank Jekyll site without any pre-installed themes:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Run the command <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">jekyll new sitename --blank</code> (replace <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">newsite</code> with the name of your site).</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">cd</code> to your new website folder.</li>
  <li>To install a Gemfile in your website directory, in a terminal or command line window, enter <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle init</code>.  This will create your Gemfile for you.</li>
  <li>At add Jekyll as a dependency, enter <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle add jekyll</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>If you are using Ruby version 3.0.0 or higher:</strong> Add webrick to your dependencies with the command <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle add webrick</code>. Otherwise, skip to the next step.</li>
  <li>To serve your website, enter <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle exec jekyll serve</code></li>
  <li>Go to your new website at <code>http://localhost:4000/</code>.</li>
</ol>
:ET